---
By: Confucius
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 198
    Verse: 14
Tags:
  - Golden Rule
---
Do not do to others as you would not like done to yourself; so there will
be no murmuring against you in the country, and none in the family; your
public life will arouse no ill-will nor your private life any resentment.
